parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a sudden loss of braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially on mountain grades or at high speeds.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and there is a complete loss of brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idle control valve can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle will not slow down when the foot is removed from the accelerator pedal
the idle control valve fails prior to service recall.
